qas.question: Name 3 artists that CBS Associated Records signed on in the 80s and 90s?

answers.text: Ozzy Osbourne, the Fabulous Thunderbirds, Electric Light Orchestra, Joan Jett, and Henry Lee Summer

qas.question: Martell Tony was the head of which label?
What label was a part of wing of sub labels at ABC?
Who didn't share the same staff as Epic Records?
Who wasn't a part of  the full CBS Records worldwide distribution system?
Ozzy Osbourne was the head of which label?

context: In the 1980s to early 1990s, there was a CBS imprint label in the US known as <b1_0><b2_0><b3_0><b4_0><b5_0>CBS Associated Records<b5_0/><b4_0/><b3_0/><b2_0/><b1_0/>. Tony Martell, veteran CBS and Epic Records A&R Vice President was head of this label and signed artists including <a0_0>Ozzy Osbourne, the Fabulous Thunderbirds, Electric Light Orchestra, Joan Jett, and Henry Lee Summer<a0_0/>. This label was a part of (Epic/Portrait/Associated) wing of sub labels at CBS which shared the same national and regional staff as the rest of Epic Records and was a part of the full CBS Records worldwide distribution system.
